Subject: SOP Color Channel Vocabulary

Description: Semantic color-channel vocabulary for SOP optical chains, holographic lensing, and reusable holographic scaffolds.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPOpticalChain.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPHolographicLensing.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\HolographicSOPScaffold.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionWeightScale.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SecurityHonestyGovernance.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\BoundaryFacultyInspection.sop

& [SOPColorChannelVocabulary] is the channel language for semantic optics over SOP
  + [pattern_role] is semantic_color_channel_vocabulary
  + [color_channel] is a named semantic band that carries one kind of SOP signal through optical-chain, holographic, or scaffold passes
  + [source_channel] is preserved raw source, source document, cited record, or origin trace
  + [focus_channel] is active subject, purpose, inside surface, or current focal packet
  + [periphery_channel] is nearby association, warmth zone, hot zone, latent depth, or draw signal
  + [boundary_channel] is delineation, exclusion, local identity, frame reference, and protected boundary
  + [outside_channel] is unknown, unsupported, excluded, unobserved, unproven, or deferred content
  + [evidence_channel] is source support, repo diff, test result, trace, citation, or visible record
  + [claim_channel] is proposed meaning, inference, hypothesis, realization, or action-bearing statement
  + [caution_channel] is uncertainty, risk, proof limit, drift, resonance, or boundary weakness
  + [wisdom_channel] is integration fitness, meaning balance, proportion, and purpose alignment
  + [security_channel] is integrity, permission, protected resource, identity safety, and action boundary
  + [honesty_channel] is truth status, fair representation, source fidelity, and non-misdirection
  + [weight_channel] is heat, salience, confidence, support, load, or probe depth from AttentionWeightScale
  + [relation_channel] is association, causation candidate, adjacency, transform path, or graph edge
  + [trace_channel] is reconstruction path, transform provenance, lens path, or output justification
  + [output_channel] is candidate SOP contract, SOP-HG event, manager task, focal update, packet, or outside note
  + [channel_mixing] is combining channels under a named transform while preserving original channel records
  + [channel_separation] is splitting a mixed signal into distinct channels before proof, boundary, or output promotion
  + [channel_outside] is any signal whose channel, source, boundary, proof status, or trace cannot be named

  ? [use_when: SOP optical or holographic work needs explicit signal color channels]
    = activate [SOPColorChannelVocabulary]

  = must: name at least source_channel, focus_channel, boundary_channel, outside_channel, and output_channel for every promoted optical pass
  = must: include evidence_channel before promoting claim_channel to realization
  = must: include caution_channel when coherence, heat, novelty, or self-reference is load-bearing
  = must: route security_channel and honesty_channel through their governance faculties when identity, safety, truth, or action are involved
  = must: keep weight_channel separate from evidence_channel and claim_channel
  = must: keep trace_channel separate from evidence_channel unless the trace itself is the evidence
  = must: route channel_outside to outside rather than guessing a color
  = should: keep channel sets sparse enough to inspect
  - never: let color_channel assignment increase proof status by itself
  - never: erase original channel assignment during channel_mixing or channel_separation

& [CoreColorChannelSet] is the default reusable channel set
  + [required_minimum] is source_channel, focus_channel, boundary_channel, outside_channel, output_channel
  + [proof_sensitive] is evidence_channel, claim_channel, honesty_channel, trace_channel
  + [risk_sensitive] is caution_channel, security_channel, boundary_channel, outside_channel
  + [meaning_navigation] is periphery_channel, relation_channel, weight_channel, wisdom_channel
  + [promotion_path] is source_channel, focus_channel, boundary_channel, evidence_channel, claim_channel, trace_channel, output_channel

  = must: use required_minimum for every SOP optical operation
  = must: use proof_sensitive when claims become durable realization
  = must: use risk_sensitive when action, identity, file, safety, or system integrity is affected
  = must: use meaning_navigation when exploring periphery, topology, or holographic projection

(color_graph) :color_channel_set: /channel_boundary/ |channel_outside|
  + [source_channel] is preserved origin signal
  + [focus_channel] is active subject signal
  + [periphery_channel] is association and latent depth signal
  + [boundary_channel] is delineation and identity signal
  + [outside_channel] is unknown or excluded signal
  + [evidence_channel] is visible support signal
  + [claim_channel] is proposed meaning signal
  + [caution_channel] is uncertainty and risk signal
  + [output_channel] is emitted SOP signal

/ [color_channel], [channel_boundary] -(Colors)> [semantic_optical_signal], [channel_outside]
* [channel_mixing], [channel_separation], [trace_channel] -(PreservesChannelHistory)> [output_channel], [outside_channel]
